<li><a href="http://www.tedpavlic.com/teaching/osu/ece209/support/opamp_basics.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.tedpavlic.com/teaching/osu/ece209/support/opamp_basics.pdf" rel="nofollow">ECE 209: Operational amplifier basics</a>&#160;– Brief document explaining zero error by naive high-gain negative feedback. Gives single OpAmp example that generalizes typical configurations.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.tedpavlic.com/teaching/osu/ece327/lab2_fets/lab2_fets_integrators.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.tedpavlic.com/teaching/osu/ece327/lab2_fets/lab2_fets_integrators.pdf" rel="nofollow">ECE 327: Practical Integrators and Operational Amplifier Offset</a>&#160;– Discusses sources of and ways of fixing offset and drift problems.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.tedpavlic.com/teaching/osu/ece327/lab3_vreg/lab3_vreg_procedure.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.tedpavlic.com/teaching/osu/ece327/lab3_vreg/lab3_vreg_procedure.pdf" rel="nofollow">ECE 327: Voltage Regulators Procedures and Explanations</a>&#160;– In the "Improving dynamic performance" section, discusses methods of using <a href="/wiki/Decoupling_capacitor" title="Decoupling capacitor">bypass capacitors</a> to improve <a href="/wiki/Power_supply_rejection_ratio" title="Power supply rejection ratio">PSRR</a> of components in designs.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.philbrickarchive.org/1964-1_v12_no1_the_lightning_empiricist.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.philbrickarchive.org/1964-1_v12_no1_the_lightning_empiricist.htm" rel="nofollow">Impedance and admittance transformations using operational amplifiers</a> by D. H. Sheingold</li>
</ul>


